div1.p: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION
In re Petition of Rose Baker for a Writ fo Habeas Corpus. )
DEMURRER OF RESPONDENT, JOHN L. SULLIVAN.
Comes now John L. Sullivan, respondent herein, and demus to the petition of the petitioner herein for a writ of habeas corpus, for the reason and upon the grounds as follows:
- I - It appears therefrom that the above entitled court has no jurisdiction of the matter set forth therein.
- II - That said petition does not state facts sufficient to entitle the petitioner to have said writ of habeas corpus issued.
div1.ab: R. S. Pierce Attorney for Respondent.
div1.p: Copy of within demurrer reviewed this 6th day of June 1912
